<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd">
<task id="task_schedule-file-ingest">
    <title>Schedule File Ingest</title>
    <shortdesc>You can have the <ph conkeyref="product-vars/gui-name"/> ingest files on a schedule
        from the <wintitle>Data Sources</wintitle> page.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <context>To schedule file ingest:</context>
        <steps id="steps_bh4_2h4_1r">
            <step>
                <cmd>Open the <uicontrol>Data Sources</uicontrol> screen, by clicking the
                        <uicontrol>Data Sources</uicontrol> icon in the left navigation bar. <image
                        href="../_images/gui-screen-shots/icon_datasources.JPG"
                        id="image_fmr_wzn_mq" scale="50"/></cmd>
                <info>
                    <p>The <wintitle>Data Sources</wintitle> page opens showing defined data
                        categories. <xref
                            href="../Data_Categories/con_data-categories.xml#concept_data-categories"
                            >Tell me about data categories.</xref></p>
                    <fig id="fig_data-sources">
                        <image href="../_images/gui-screen-shots/data-sources.png"
                            id="image_hmp_55r_3q" scale="50"/>
                    </fig>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click any data category to expand the category and see the data sources
                    included in the category.</cmd>
                <info>
                    <fig id="fig_data-sources_data-sources">
                        <image href="../_images/gui-screen-shots/data-sources_data-sources.png"
                            id="image_wpx_pd4_mq" scale="50"/>
                    </fig>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click the data source name. The <wintitle>Data Policy</wintitle> screen for the
                    data source opens.</cmd>
                <info>
                    <fig id="fig_data-policy-cmplt">
                        <image href="../_images/gui-screen-shots/data-sources_data-policy_cmplt.png"
                            id="image_i2r_ck4_1r" scale="50"/>
                    </fig>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Ingest Data</uicontrol> tab.</cmd>
                <info/>
                <info>The <wintitle>Ingest Data</wintitle> screen opens.<fig id="fig_ingest-data">
                        <image href="../_images/gui-screen-shots/data-sources_ingest-data.png"
                            id="image_bnx_xzv_1r" scale="50"/>
                    </fig></info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Choose File</uicontrol> button (or
                        <uicontrol>Browse</uicontrol> button, depending on your browser). Navigate
                    to the folder and select the file or files you want to ingest. Click the
                        <uicontrol>Choose</uicontrol> or <uicontrol>Open</uicontrol> button to set
                    your selection.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>For structured or composite file such as a ZIP files or CSV files, if you want
                    the PHEMI system DPFs to automatically process the file on ingest, click the
                    drop-down arrow in the <uicontrol>Ingest Composite Data</uicontrol> field and
                    select the file type from the list. If you want <ph
                        conkeyref="product-vars/product-name"/> to store the original data along
                    with the derived data items, check the <uicontrol>Store Original
                        File</uicontrol> checkbox.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>In the <uicontrol>Scheduled</uicontrol> pane, choose from
                        <uicontrol>Hourly</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>Daily</uicontrol>, or
                        <uicontrol>Weekly</uicontrol> ingest schedule.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Select one of <uicontrol>API-JSON</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>SFTP</uicontrol>,
                        <uicontrol>SMB/Samba</uicontrol>, or <uicontrol>ODBC</uicontrol> as the
                    format of the ingested files.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Configure</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Ingest Files</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
                <info><ph conkeyref="product-vars/product-name"/> ingests the files and continues to
                    ingest files automatically on the specified schedule.</info>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
